  <data key="d1">self_definition</data>
  <data key="d2">none</data>
  <data key="d3">The
gas ﬂow is in the steady state (@p
A/@t /C25 0) and the diffusion
equation is simpliﬁed to
Deff
@2pA x; tðÞ
@x2 /C25 0: (17)
Its solution is
pA x; tðÞ ¼ pA0 1 /C0 x
xs
/C18/C19
; x &lt; xt; (18)
where the boundary conditionspA(0,t) ¼pA0 and pA(xs,t) /C25 0
have been used.xt is the limit beyond which the approximation
g /C25 0 is not valid andxs describes how far the reactant front
has propagated at timet.</data>
  <data key="d4">text_definition</data>
  <data key="d5"></data>
</edge>
