  <data key="d4">equation</data>
  <data key="d5"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="x" target="x">
  <data key="d1">self_definition</data>
  <data key="d2">none</data>
  <data key="d3">COMPARISON WITH THE GORDON MODEL
In the Gordon model for ALD conformality, it is
assumed that the gas enters the rectangular channel (height
H /C28 width W) as a front with a constant concentration with-
out any gas diffusion in the propagation direction (x-axis).</data>
  <data key="d4">text_definition</data>
  <data key="d5"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="x" target="g[pc]">
  <data key="d1">text_affects</data>
  <data key="d2">unknown</data>
  <data key="d3">If the thickness growth of the ﬁlm in one complete
growth cycle isgpc, the free height of the channel afterN
cycles is
HNðÞ ¼ H 0ðÞ /C0 2N gpc: (35)
Because the ﬁlm growth thickness depends on locationx, the
channel height also varies with location.</data>
  <data key="d4">text</data>
  <data key="d5"></data>
</edge>
