  <data key="d3">Whenq is the saturation areal
density ( m
/C0 2) of the adsorbed molecules, the number
of adsorbed molecules at distancedx in a channel with width
W is
dN ¼ 2qWdx: (38)
On the other hand, the number of molecules is equal to the
ﬂow F (1/s) of incoming gas in timedt
dN ¼ Fdt: (39)
When the surface is saturated, there is no absorption and this
location x propagates with velocityv
v ¼ dx
